definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Select a namespace for the term.
note.ISO:639:3:eng: You may omit the namespace if you are defining a namespace, in all other cases you must provide the namespace.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide a unique code for the term.
The term global identifier code.
Provide an internet address that can be considered the public term identifier.
This value will be used as a variable name when referring to the current term.
Provide relevant keywords that apply to the term.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: These keywords will be used when searching for terms.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: This value corresponds to the highest user rank that is allowed to manage the term.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Users with a rank lower than the selected value will not be allowed to modify or enter the value; if the rank is omitted all users are authorised..

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Select the roles that will allow the display and modification of the term.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Some terms may be restricted to specific roles, if you omit this field all roles apply, if you provide a selection, only the selected roles will be able to access the term.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Select the implementation category that applies to the term.
Select the term status.

description.ISO:639:3:eng: Select the setting that applies when creating or modifying the term.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide a name or label for the term.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: This string will be used as the input label or table header for the term.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide a definition for the term.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: The definition will be displayed as a popover when the cursor hovers the term label.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide a detailed description for the term.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: The description can be used to add all relevant information that was not included in the definition.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide side notes as relevant.
Provide examples if relevant.
Term domain.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: The domain is the highest level category that classifies the term.
note.ISO:639:3:eng: The domain can be used to focus term searches.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: This list indicates all the contexts in which the term was used.
Term category.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: The category is a classification below the domain.
note.ISO:639:3:eng: The category can be used to focus term searches within a domain.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide relevant internet addresses where additional information and references for the term can be found.

description.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide the symbol that applies to the term, if available.
Provide all known synonyms with which the current term may be referenced.
Provide an SVG image that can be used as the icon or logo for the current term, if applicable.
Select the field that will be used to sort the template elements.
Select the standard unit that applies to the controlled vocabulary, if applicable.
Select all other standard units that may apply to the controlled vocabulary, if applicable.
Select the field that will be used to sort the controlled vocabulary elements.
Select the standard unit that applies to the controlled vocabulary element, if applicable.
Select all other standard units that may apply to the controlled vocabulary element, if applicable.
Provide the hierarchy level that applies to the current controlled vocabulary element.
Select the field that will be used to sort the category elements.
Select the storage type of the collection.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Collection where the instance is stored.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Select the collection that will contain instances of this type.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Instance structure class.
description.ISO:639:3:eng: Select the class defining the instance data structure.
Select the instance to which the data type refers to.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide the minimum and maximum length of the text value for this data type, if applicable.
Provide the regular expression to validate the text value for this data type, if applicable.

description.ISO:639:3:eng: Select the instance to which the data type refers to.

definition.ISO:639:3:eng: Provide the minimum and maximum range for values of this data type, if applicable.

description.ISO:639:3:eng: Select the instance to which the data type refers to.
Select the direction of directed graph edges associated with the current predicate.
example.ISO:639:3:eng: For instance, a predicate that implies membership can be expressed in two ways: a member-of predicate would imply that the source of the relationship is a member of the relationship destination, while a group-of predicate would imply that the source of the relationship is the membership group of the destination of the relationship.

description.ISO:639:3:eng: If the class is top level, select the instance to which it refers to.
Provide the internet address where the schema of the current class can be found.
Select the field that will be used to sort the structure elements.
Provide the internet address where the schema of the current structure can be found.
Select the relevant option applicable when including a form.
Select which object instance this form takes its data, if the form is associated with a single instance.
Select the field that will be used to sort the form elements.
